Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.22,0:00:21.22,generic,,0,0,0,,{\an7}{\pos(88.594,21.429)}Aired on Heisei 6 (1994), December 18th
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.22,0:00:02.82,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Annual Kohaku battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.62,0:00:03.82,hamada,,0,0,0,,{\pos(540,600)}{\fs35}I'll go with white
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.02,0:00:08.74,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\pos(540,600)}{\fs35}Then, me too...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.74,0:00:09.62,hamada,,0,0,0,,{\pos(540,600)}{\fs35}No, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.22,0:00:14.82,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Both wanted to bet for the white team! They then played a game for a decision!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.42,0:00:21.62,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hamada wins! Hamada bets on the white team while Matsumoto bets on red!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.62,0:00:22.02,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\alpha&HFF}BUGFIX
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.74,0:00:28.62,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(540,600)}{\3c&H1133AA&}Heisei 6, December 31st
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.22,0:00:25.22,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And there comes decisive December 31st...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.22,0:00:33.42,generic,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Note: Yakyuken is a strip game with rock-paper-scissors and baseball themed chant.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.22,0:00:33.42,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Everyone arose at Yakyuken party, but they were preoccupied with the result of the battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.42,0:00:37.82,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\alpha&HFF}BUGFIX
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.82,0:00:40.22,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As soon as they finished shooting for the show, they went into the waiting room!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.34,0:00:45.82,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\pos(540,600)}{\fs35}YEAHHHHHHHHHH!!!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.82,0:00:49.62,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The red team won! Victory for Matsumoto! Batsu Game for Hamada!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.22,0:00:49.62,title,,0,0,0,,{\frz12}{\pos(565,535)}Batsu game for loser Hamada!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.62,0:00:53.62,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(540,291)}{\fs65}{\fnVerdana}{\alpha&H22}March 1st
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.42,0:00:53.62,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And now, in March 1st, the time has come!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.22,0:00:57.42,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(540,582.857)}Board room
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.62,0:00:57.42,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A usual day for Gaki board room...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.34,0:01:22.42,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\an1}{\fs35}{\pos(105.469,548.571)}{\1c&HDD5533&}GnT Special Program
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.34,0:01:22.42,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\an1}{\fs35}{\pos(105.469,600)}{\1c&H3333BB&}Hama-chan Batsu Game
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.82,0:00:58.74,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Tired, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.74,0:01:00.22,hosei,,0,0,0,,Yeah, tired!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.82,0:01:01.42,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,He's late!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.42,0:01:04.42,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Here he comes, here he comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.02,0:01:09.22,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Well, you've done well enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.62,0:01:16.22,hosei,,0,0,0,,Did you really think the white team can win?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.22,0:01:19.22,hamada,,0,0,0,,Uh, yeah. That's what I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.62,0:01:21.82,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Are you reading the trend of time?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.82,0:01:26.22,hamada,,0,0,0,,Well, I didn't think that deeply to say for the white team..
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.42,0:01:29.62,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Can you read it? Can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.62,0:01:32.22,hamada,,0,0,0,,The fact that the white team lost makes I couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.22,0:01:33.22,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.22,0:01:37.62,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Well, if you got something, keep in touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.02,0:01:39.42,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Tell him my number.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.42,0:01:41.22,hosei,,0,0,0,,Ok, your phone number...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.22,0:01:44.02,hosei,,0,0,0,,Should I give him the office number instead? It'd bad if he gotten your phone number.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.02,0:01:47.42,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,You're right! He's gonna prank me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.62,0:01:51.22,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Huh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.62,0:01:52.62,hosei,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.82,0:01:56.82,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I can't find my mechanical pencil.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.22,0:02:01.02,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,No, no, that won't do. I need my mechanical pencil, I cannot write with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.02,0:02:02.82,hamada,,0,0,0,,Cannot write with that!? Sure you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.02,0:02:06.02,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Where did it go...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.22,0:02:09.42,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Ah! I remember it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.42,0:02:13.02,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sakamoto borrowed it from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.14,0:02:15.62,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(253.125,621.429)}Sakamoto Ryuichi
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.22,0:02:16.02,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(253.125,621.429)}{\alpha&HFF}BUGFIX
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.22,0:02:16.82,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.22,0:02:20.02,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I can't do this without it!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.42,0:02:23.22,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Go fetch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.02,0:02:26.62,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Go and fetch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.62,0:02:29.42,hamada,,0,0,0,,You can find mechanical pencils anywhere! Just go buy one yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.42,0:02:33.02,matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Go to New York and fetch my mechanical pencil from Mr. Sakamoto!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.90,0:02:40.30,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\1c&H0000AA&}Batsu Game: {\1c&H00AA00&}Hama-chan goes to New York {\1c&H00BBBB&}to fetch a mechanical pencil!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.30,0:02:47.30,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Immediately and forcibly, after his first batsu game that took place in foreign country, "Hamada's journey to France for Evian water"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.90,0:02:50.90,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(540,600)}Hamada sulking in bed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.30,0:02:49.10,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He now has to do another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.10,0:02:52.50,generic2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}With 12 hours of flight ahead of him, a cruel trip starts for Hamada!
